MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience equivalent to the next lower grade level (GS/GG-11) or pay band in the federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector performing duties such as:
1) Developing and implementing policies and establishes safety plans and procedures;
2) Inspecting all areas under organization purview for conformity to safety rules standards and regulations;
3) Detecting hazardous and undesirable operating conditions to originate and recommends corrective action.;
4) Investigating and analyzing material damage and personal injury accidents in accordance with policies, practices and procedures. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/0000/safety-and-occupational-health-management-series-0018/
